
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "FAQ";
}

<script type="text/javascript">
    $(document).ready(function () {
        $("#faq").addClass("active");
    });
</script>




    <h3 style="font-weight:500;text-align:center;background-color:darkorange;color:white">Frequently Asked Questions</h3>

    <div class="alert alert-info" style="border:1px solid lightGrey; margin-right:10px">
        This section contains a wealth of information, related to <strong>@Session["CustomerName"]</strong> and its online store. If you cannot find an answer to your question,
        make sure to contact us at <a href="mailto:onlinesales@verser.com.au">onlinesales@verser.com.au</a>.
    </div>
    <div style="border:solid;border-color:grey;border-width:thin;padding-left:20px" >
        <br />
        <p ><strong>Q. What round of disposals does the service cover?</strong></p>
        <div>A. Round 1, cycle 6 (R1C6)</div>
        <br />

        <p><strong>Q. What happens with my notebook once collected?</strong></p>
        <div >
            A: Verser will collect all notebooks and return to our facility in Campbellfield where certified data @*<br />*@
            destruction services are performed. We then re-image before shipping.
        </div>
        <br />

        <p><strong>Q. How many notebooks can I purchase?</strong></p>
        <div>
            A: The Department has facilitated a program with Verser to offer teachers to purchase the notebook @*<br />*@
            you were previously using in round R1C6.
        </div>
        <br />

        <p><strong>Q. Will I receive my own notebook?</strong></p>
        <div>
            A: Yes. The exception to this standard is if an operational fault is identified at the time of the data wipe @*<br />*@
            or re-imaging.
        </div>
        <br />

        <p><strong>Q. What happens if my notebook is found to be faulty?</strong></p>
        <div>
            A: Verser will contact you directly to advise as such and offer you options of a like-for-like @*<br />*@
            replacement or a full refund.
        </div>
        <br />

        <p><strong>Q. Where will my notebook be sent?</strong></p>
        <div>A: Your notebook will be sent back to the address you specify during your purchase.</div>
        <br />

        <p><strong>Q. Will Microsoft Office be loaded on my notebook?</strong></p>
        <div>A: No, Microsoft Office is not part of the agreed process.</div>
        <br />

        <p><strong>Q. What happens if my notebook doesn't work when I receive it?</strong></p>
        <div>
            A: Verser will offer a 10-day warranty period starting from the date of delivery for any notebooks@*<br />*@
            received as DOA (dead on arrival). Please contact Verser at <a href="mailto:Det.enquires@verser.com.au">Det.enquires@verser.com.au</a> and we'll <br />
            contact you to offer you a like-for-like replacement or a full refund.
        </div>
        <br />

        <p><strong>Q. Will the notebook I receive have all my data?</strong></p>
        <div>
            A: No, if you wish to retain personal data, it is your responsibility to back-up to an external device @*<br />*@
            prior to the collection. Verser does not accept responsibility for loss of data.
        </div>
        <br />

        <p><strong>Q. What happens if I have any further questions?</strong></p>
        <div>A: Please email <a href="mailto:Det.enquires@verser.com.au">Det.enquires@verser.com.au</a></div>
        <br />
    </div>